column4: Welcome, you are now talking to an AI doctor. As I am part of a scientific experiment, I would appreciate it if you could take the time to answer a super short questionnaire at the end of the interview. Tap Speak to ask your question and then tap Send to submit it to me.
i'm feeling a headache yeah it's it's better for you yeah hello can i ask the question now yeah i'm feeling a headache what can i do

Hi there- are you currently experiencing a headache? If so, have you noticed any other symptoms associated with it, such as nausea or visual disturbances? In the meantime, try to remain hydrated and get enough rest. Pain relievers such as ibuprofen or acetaminophen are also helpful in relieving some headache symptoms.
I'm feeling just the head, head headache and maybe it's about the irritation.

It sounds like you may be experiencing a tension headache which can be caused by a variety of factors- such as stress, poor posture, dehydration, or lack of sleep. To help alleviate the symptoms, it is important to practice good posture, get enough rest, and manage stress. Regular exercise can also be beneficial. You can take over the counter medications such as ibuprofen or acetaminophen for pain relief. Additionally, relaxation techniques such as meditation or yoga may help reduce the overall level of tension.
